{
  "text": "This population-based study was conducted in Tehran, Iran (Latitude: 35\u00b0 North, Longitude: 51\u00b0 East). The weather is typically sunny, with average annual bright sunshine of 2,800 h and an annual mean cloud cover of 30%. The average elevation is approximately 1,200 m above sea level, and the city covers a large area of 613 km 2 . Tehran has an urban resident population of over 8.2 million people, though the daytime population has been estimated at more than 10 million people due to diurnal migration from the outlying areas [13, [CITATION_1] .",
